<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Calling setRedirect on a Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract-based Class (like Zend_Controller_Response_Http) does not set the _isRedirect-Flag.</p>

<p>There would be at least 2 Ways to fix this.</p>

<p>1) setting _isRedirect in the setRedirect-Method
2) setting _isRedirect in setHeader if the header-name matches 'Location', like it is done in setRawHeader() already.</p>

<p>Will attach Patch + Unittest for version 1) and 2) soon.</p>

<p>If version 2) does not break anything for compatibility-reasons in setHeader() it would be my prefered way because it adds the functionality which already exists in setRawHeader(), which would be more consistent.</p>

